36#include <config.h>
37
38#include <krb5/roken.h>
39
40ROKEN_LIB_FUNCTION int ROKEN_LIB_CALL
41roken_concat (char *s, size_t len, ...)
42{
43 int ret;
44 va_list args;
45
46 va_start(args, len);
47 ret = roken_vconcat (s, len, args);
48 va_end(args);
49 return ret;
50}
51
52ROKEN_LIB_FUNCTION int ROKEN_LIB_CALL
53roken_vconcat (char *s, size_t len, va_list args)
54{
55 const char *a;
56
57 while ((a = va_arg(args, const char*))) {
58 size_t n = strlen (a);
59
60 if (n >= len)
61 return -1;
62 memcpy (s, a, n);
63 s += n;
64 len -= n;
65 }
66 *s = '\0';
67 return 0;
68}
69
70ROKEN_LIB_FUNCTION size_t ROKEN_LIB_CALL
71roken_vmconcat (char **s, size_t max_len, va_list args)
72{
73 const char *a;
74 char *p, *q;
75 size_t len = 0;
76 *s = NULL;
77 p = malloc(1);
78 if(p == NULL)
79 return 0;
80 len = 1;
81 while ((a = va_arg(args, const char*))) {
82 size_t n = strlen (a);
83
84 if(max_len && len + n > max_len){
85 free(p);
86 return 0;
87 }
88 q = realloc(p, len + n);
89 if(q == NULL){
90 free(p);
91 return 0;
92 }
93 p = q;
94 memcpy (p + len - 1, a, n);
95 len += n;
96 }
97 p[len - 1] = '\0';
98 *s = p;
99 return len;
100}
101
102ROKEN_LIB_FUNCTION size_t ROKEN_LIB_CALL
103roken_mconcat (char **s, size_t max_len, ...)
104{
105 size_t ret;
106 va_list args;
107
108 va_start(args, max_len);
109 ret = roken_vmconcat (s, max_len, args);
110 va_end(args);
111 return ret;
112}
